<se_low>Chief: Gojoshar! Welcome to Empycchu. You've seen our village, yes? Then let me tell you something.
<se_low>Chief: I assume the others have told you that Empyrea was all responsible for the attack on our village.
<se_low>Chief: It is natural to think this. But to be honest, I am not fully convinced that she wished to cause us any harm.
<se_low>Chief: Since times of old Empyrea has been venerated by the people of Empycchu.<page>Chief: It was not simply because she was pretty. It was because she has protected us.
<se_low>Chief: I beg of you. Will you find out why Empyrea continues to attack us? I believe there is some hidden meaning behind her actions.
<se_low>Chief: I also believe that your arrival here is not an accident. I believe it to be fate.
<se_low>Chief: Only Empyrea may cross between the World of Darkness and the World of Light. It was she who guided you here, correct?
<se_low>Chief: Then, Empyrea must be thinking something. She may reveal the truth to you.<page>Chief: I apologise for putting such a burden on your shoulders.
